===Noun===
'''energy''' (''plural:'' [[energies]])

#The [[impetus]] behind all [[motion]] and all [[activity]].  
#(''physics'') [[Work]], measured in the [[metric]] system with units of [[joule]]s (MKS) or [[erg]]s (CGS).  Other units for measuring energy include [[foot]]-[[pound-force|pound]], [[BTU]], [[kilowatt-hour]], and the [[calorie]].  Energy is the product (integral) of power and time.
#*'''Units:'''
#::[[SI]]: [[joule]] (J), [[kilowatt-hour]] (kW·h)<!--in a strict sense, hours are not part of SI but are acceptable for use with SI-->
#::Customary: [[foot]]-[[pound-force]], [[calorie]], [[kilocalorie]] (i.e. dietary calories), [[BTU]], [[liter]]-[[atmosphere]], [[ton of TNT]] 


